Thank you. You're getting wet.

265
00:13:01,405 --> 00:13:02,323
I'm okay.

266
00:13:02,406 --> 00:13:03,783
- It's pouring.
- Which way?

267
00:13:03,866 --> 00:13:05,409
- That way?
- That way.

268
00:13:05,493 --> 00:13:06,744
- Let's go that way.
- Yeah.

269
00:13:06,827 --> 00:13:08,704
- Oh, no.
- Let's go.

270
00:13:08,788 --> 00:13:10,539
Thank you.

271
00:13:10,623 --> 00:13:13,501
- Sorry. It was sunny a minute ago.
- I know.

272
00:13:13,584 --> 00:13:15,961
- These two are adorable.
- They're so cute.

273
00:13:16,045 --> 00:13:17,630
They're so sweet.

274
00:13:21,342 --> 00:13:22,468
Thank you.

275
00:13:22,551 --> 00:13:24,428
Oh, no. I need to thank you.

276
00:13:24,512 --> 00:13:25,346
Thank you.

277
00:13:25,429 --> 00:13:28,015
- For the letter.
- Oh, yeah.

278
00:13:28,098 --> 00:13:30,768
I hadn't met anybody.

279
00:13:30,851 --> 00:13:34,772
I thought I had to do something.

280
00:13:36,106 --> 00:13:37,316
Yours was in the middle.

281
00:13:37,399 --> 00:13:38,859
- That's why?
- So I posted there.

282
00:13:38,943 --> 00:13:39,777
Oh.

283
00:13:40,861 --> 00:13:42,154
I was lucky.

284
00:13:42,238 --> 00:13:45,282
We all gathered last night, right?

285
00:13:46,158 --> 00:13:50,454
- You seemed the most approachable.
- Really?

286
00:13:50,538 --> 00:13:53,874
- That ambience got us nervous, didn't it?
- Yeah.

287
00:13:53,958 --> 00:13:56,502
I knew we should get ourselves talking.

288
00:13:57,253 --> 00:14:00,631
I said I felt comfortable in the silence.

289
00:14:00,714 --> 00:14:03,259
- And you agreed with me.
- Yeah.

290
00:14:03,759 --> 00:14:07,012
- You gave me that letter, right?
- Yeah.

291
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:10,558
- Of course, I was happy and came today.
- Yeah.

292
00:14:11,058 --> 00:14:13,185
Even without that letter,
I would've asked you.

293
00:14:13,269 --> 00:14:14,103
What?

294
00:14:14,186 --> 00:14:15,813
I would have asked you out.

295
00:14:16,522 --> 00:14:18,816
- What? Oh, really? Thank you.
- Yeah.

296
00:14:18,899 --> 00:14:22,444
I felt the same way yesterday.

297
00:14:24,363 --> 00:14:26,323
That makes me happy. Thanks.

298
00:14:26,407 --> 00:14:27,575
- What a relief.
- Yeah.

299
00:14:28,075 --> 00:14:29,827
He's not afraid to speak his mind.

300
00:14:29,910 --> 00:14:31,328
That's true. He does.

301
00:14:32,371 --> 00:14:33,873
- About yesterday…
- Yeah?

302
00:14:36,125 --> 00:14:37,793
That was the first time…

303
00:14:41,964 --> 00:14:44,592
I ever asked somebody on a date.

304
00:14:46,260 --> 00:14:47,136
Seriously?

305
00:14:47,636 --> 00:14:49,179
You're okay with me?

306
00:14:49,263 --> 00:14:50,097
Yeah.

307
00:14:51,140 --> 00:14:52,725
I've never said that to anyone.

308
00:14:52,808 --> 00:14:53,809
Does everyone say it?

309
00:14:54,310 --> 00:14:56,812
- I guess we hardly ever say it.
- Right?

310
00:14:56,896 --> 00:14:57,938
I mean,

311
00:14:58,981 --> 00:15:02,526
if we had our phones,
we could just text and ask people out.

312
00:15:02,610 --> 00:15:04,361
For dinner or to a café.

313
00:15:04,445 --> 00:15:08,365
But to ask someone out
on a date in person?

314
00:15:09,617 --> 00:15:10,701
We don't do that.

315
00:15:12,202 --> 00:15:13,370
I was nervous.

316
00:15:13,871 --> 00:15:15,331
I really appreciate it.

317
00:15:17,082 --> 00:15:18,876
Thank you for coming.

318
00:15:20,377 --> 00:15:21,754
- Did you like it?
- Yeah.

319
00:15:22,296 --> 00:15:23,631
That's good to know.

320
00:15:23,714 --> 00:15:25,007
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

321
00:15:25,090 --> 00:15:25,925
"Yeah"?

322
00:15:27,885 --> 00:15:29,470
- You're fast.
- Okay.

323
00:15:30,137 --> 00:15:33,015
I can't help it.
This tiny umbrella is shaped like this.

324
00:15:33,515 --> 00:15:36,352
- Like this.
- I think we go this way.

325
00:15:36,852 --> 00:15:40,147
I have a feeling
that we should go this way.

326
00:15:40,230 --> 00:15:41,148
A feeling?

327
00:15:41,231 --> 00:15:43,150
I'm not even looking at the map.

328
00:15:44,193 --> 00:15:45,736
I can't read maps.

329
00:15:46,737 --> 00:15:49,615
She said it was her first time
asking somebody out on a date.

330
00:15:49,698 --> 00:15:50,574
She did.

331
00:15:50,658 --> 00:15:52,618
That's Tohko's "first-time" tactic.

332
00:15:53,285 --> 00:15:54,328
Did she use it before?

333
00:15:54,411 --> 00:15:57,289
- She said she's never dated anybody.
- Oh, right.

334
00:15:57,373 --> 00:16:00,668
- That might put pressure on some people.
- That's true.

335
00:16:00,751 --> 00:16:04,797
She doesn't necessarily
have to say it's her first time.

336
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:08,550
- Yudai kind of gives light reactions.
- He does.

337
00:16:08,634 --> 00:16:10,636
- We don't see his true feelings.
- No.

338
00:16:10,719 --> 00:16:12,930
- He gives good responses.
- Yeah.

339
00:16:13,013 --> 00:16:14,139
And Yudai.

340
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:16,058
Before his date…

341
00:16:16,141 --> 00:16:18,268
<i>- He wrote a letter.</i>
<i>- To Nanami.</i>

342
00:16:18,352 --> 00:16:20,312
<i>- Yes, to Nanami.</i>
<i>- What will happen?</i>

343
00:16:20,396 --> 00:16:24,066
So, Nanami and Kensuke…

344
00:16:24,149 --> 00:16:27,361
Will they come back
and check their mailboxes?

345
00:16:27,444 --> 00:16:28,320
That's true.

346
00:16:28,404 --> 00:16:29,738
Right?

347
00:16:29,822 --> 00:16:31,198
They're on a date.

348
00:16:31,281 --> 00:16:33,325
And Kensuke forgot his umbrella.

349
00:16:33,409 --> 00:16:35,035
- What was that?
- I'm sorry.

350
00:16:35,119 --> 00:16:36,120
<i>But why?</i>

351
00:16:36,203 --> 00:16:38,330
<i>- Plus, he was late.</i>
<i>- Yeah.</i>

352
00:16:38,414 --> 00:16:40,666
- He must have been sleeping.
- He probably was.

353
00:16:40,749 --> 00:16:42,584
I can't think of any other reason.

354
00:16:42,668 --> 00:16:44,586
- Comedians are like that.
- We're impulsive.

355
00:16:44,670 --> 00:16:46,130
"Do you wanna go anywhere?"

356
00:16:46,630 --> 00:16:48,966
"Let's go there.
That way? That way. Let's go."

357
00:16:49,049 --> 00:16:50,092
Comedians are like that.

358
00:16:50,175 --> 00:16:52,052
- But Kensuke told Nanami.
- Yes.

359
00:16:52,136 --> 00:16:54,304
- He would've asked her out.
- Yes.

360
00:16:54,388 --> 00:16:57,141
- He says those things clearly.
- He does.

361
00:16:57,224 --> 00:17:00,019
- He's got talent for a kept man.
- That's true!

362
00:17:00,102 --> 00:17:01,270
That Kensuke.

363
00:17:01,353 --> 00:17:02,312
Also, Kanaka and Sho.

364
00:17:02,396 --> 00:17:03,564
Right. They're good.

365
00:17:03,647 --> 00:17:05,315
- In Provence.
- It's the Wish Letter.

366
00:17:05,399 --> 00:17:08,193
<i>The weather cleared up,</i>
<i>and they climbed to the top.</i>

367
00:17:08,277 --> 00:17:11,155
There's nothing too special,
but they look comfortable.

368
00:17:11,238 --> 00:17:13,323
- Yeah, that's true.
- Comfortable together.

369
00:17:13,407 --> 00:17:16,201
- And Mimi and Atsushi are in Cannes.
- Yes.

370
00:17:16,285 --> 00:17:19,246
<i>- She wanted to share the umbrella.</i>
<i>- Yeah.</i>

371
00:17:19,329 --> 00:17:20,789
She said that to Aru.

372
00:17:22,207 --> 00:17:23,042
Aru.

373
00:17:23,125 --> 00:17:24,877
<i>- The cap and stickers.</i>
<i>- The must-haves.</i>

374
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:25,919
<i>Mimi loves that.</i>

375
00:17:26,003 --> 00:17:27,713
<i>- </i>She loves local stuff.
- Loves them.

376
00:17:27,796 --> 00:17:28,672
She buys them all.

377
00:17:28,756 --> 00:17:30,966
And today is Day Four.

378
00:17:31,050 --> 00:17:34,261
So the ones
with Wish Letters for Day Five,

379
00:17:34,344 --> 00:17:36,472
meaning Tohko and Yudai,

380
00:17:36,555 --> 00:17:40,934
must hand their letters
or exchange them with somebody today.

381
00:17:41,018 --> 00:17:42,436
- That's the rule.
- Right.

382
00:17:42,519 --> 00:17:46,023
- Exchanging at this time is tough.
- You're right.

383
00:17:46,106 --> 00:17:48,650
The one with this letter
needs to act quickly.

384
00:17:48,734 --> 00:17:51,195
And everybody's out and about.

385
00:18:01,288 --> 00:18:02,122
Oh!

386
00:18:02,790 --> 00:18:04,500
- We're here.
- This, huh?

387
00:18:05,751 --> 00:18:07,419
- Yay!
- Wow.

388
00:18:07,503 --> 00:18:08,420
- Look.
- What?

389
00:18:08,504 --> 00:18:09,963
It's the market.

390
00:18:10,047 --> 00:18:11,173
Oh, this is it.

391
00:18:11,256 --> 00:18:12,633
It's this!

392
00:18:12,716 --> 00:18:13,550
Wow!

393
00:18:14,051 --> 00:18:15,260
This is amazing.

394
00:18:17,971 --> 00:18:19,598
It smells so nice.

395
00:18:19,681 --> 00:18:22,351
- Can I get this paella?
- I wanna eat it too.

396
00:18:23,727 --> 00:18:25,979
- Merci beaucoup.
- Merci beaucoup.

397
00:18:26,063 --> 00:18:28,398
- See you. Have a nice day.
- Have a nice day.

398
00:18:28,482 --> 00:18:29,399
Have a nice day.

399
00:18:29,483 --> 00:18:31,610
Hey, look. This looks delicious.

400
00:18:32,111 --> 00:18:34,571
- Recommendation?
- Yes, it's very nice.

401
00:18:35,072 --> 00:18:37,866
- I'll take this.
- You want one of these?

402
00:18:40,911 --> 00:18:42,579
Do you want to taste the hummus?

403
00:18:42,663 --> 00:18:43,914
- Yes.
- Yeah?

404
00:18:47,292 --> 00:18:48,335
Can I?

405
00:18:52,923 --> 00:18:55,050
- Oh, that looks tasty.
- Yeah.

406
00:18:55,134 --> 00:18:56,468
That's awesome.

407
00:18:56,969 --> 00:18:57,928
Do you smell that?

408
00:18:58,428 --> 00:18:59,972
- Nice smell.
- Yeah, nice smell.

409
00:19:01,723 --> 00:19:03,976
- Mimi's in a good mood.
- Yeah.

410
00:19:04,059 --> 00:19:08,063
- It's great how she enjoys every moment.
- I totally agree.

411
00:19:11,150 --> 00:19:12,359
I'm hungry.

412
00:19:12,442 --> 00:19:13,443
Yeah, me too.

413
00:19:13,527 --> 00:19:15,320
We've been walking all day today.

414
00:19:15,404 --> 00:19:17,156
But I'm not tired at all.

415
00:19:17,239 --> 00:19:18,448
Please take a seat.

416
00:19:18,532 --> 00:19:19,366
Thanks.

417
00:19:20,409 --> 00:19:21,869
- Wow.
- Yeah.

418
00:19:21,952 --> 00:19:22,786
Look at that.

419
00:19:24,872 --> 00:19:26,123
That's what we climbed.

420
00:19:26,623 --> 00:19:28,959
- We climbed up to that corner.
- Wow.

421
00:19:29,960 --> 00:19:31,170
Have you found anybody?

422
00:19:31,879 --> 00:19:34,798
- Hmm.
- You met everybody last night, right?

423
00:19:34,882 --> 00:19:37,801
- I did want to talk more with you.
- Oh, really?

424
00:19:37,885 --> 00:19:40,053
We sat next to each other, remember?

425
00:19:40,137 --> 00:19:42,431
- We chatted while we ate.
- Yeah.

426
00:19:42,514 --> 00:19:45,517
I wanted to talk with you more.

427
00:19:45,601 --> 00:19:48,145
- So today was a good chance.
- Oh.

428
00:19:48,937 --> 00:19:49,813
I'm glad I asked.

429
00:19:49,897 --> 00:19:52,983
Your manly behavior really impressed me.

430
00:19:53,066 --> 00:19:53,901
Really?

431
00:19:53,984 --> 00:19:56,236
I thought it was really cool

432
00:19:56,320 --> 00:19:58,989
that you asked me out
in front of everybody.

433
00:19:59,072 --> 00:20:04,036
It's been two years?
No, three years since I had a boyfriend.

434
00:20:04,119 --> 00:20:05,120
Oh, really?

435
00:20:05,204 --> 00:20:07,664
Yeah. During that time,
I went on dates and stuff,

436
00:20:07,748 --> 00:20:11,335
and it almost got serious
with some people too.

437
00:20:11,418 --> 00:20:16,298
But it's really hard to find a guy
that could act as manly as you.

438
00:20:16,798 --> 00:20:18,008
Maybe that's true.

439
00:20:18,717 --> 00:20:21,011
- Manly guys, huh?
- They're an endangered species.

440
00:20:23,013 --> 00:20:25,933
He doesn't say, "Well, I can pull it off."

441
00:20:26,850 --> 00:20:29,645
Sho tends to do that, doesn't he?

442
00:20:29,728 --> 00:20:31,980
He doesn't take that next step.

443
00:20:32,064 --> 00:20:33,398
I'll eat first.

444
00:20:33,482 --> 00:20:34,566
- Let's eat.
- Let's eat.

445
00:20:37,819 --> 00:20:38,654
This is good.

446
00:20:38,737 --> 00:20:41,740
What was your favorite food in Nice?

447
00:20:41,823 --> 00:20:43,116
The truffle risotto.

448
00:20:43,742 --> 00:20:44,701
My number one.

449
00:20:44,785 --> 00:20:47,162
That was insanely delicious.

450
00:20:47,246 --> 00:20:48,413
I want you to try it.

451
00:20:48,497 --> 00:20:51,208
Yeah. But don't you want to
try other places?

452
00:20:51,291 --> 00:20:53,627
Yeah, let's go find other places.

453
00:20:53,710 --> 00:20:54,711
Let's do that.

454
00:20:55,462 --> 00:20:56,588
- You know what?
- Yeah?

455
00:20:56,672 --> 00:21:00,759
There are people going on trips
with the Wish Letter today.

456
00:21:00,842 --> 00:21:02,052
What day was yours?

457
00:21:02,135 --> 00:21:03,929
Mine was eight. Day Eight.

458
00:21:04,429 --> 00:21:05,264
That's late.

459
00:21:05,347 --> 00:21:06,848
- The last one.
- The last one?

460
00:21:06,932 --> 00:21:07,766
Yeah.

461
00:21:08,308 --> 00:21:09,726
- That's nice.
- How about you?

462
00:21:09,810 --> 00:21:12,312
- Mine was Day Six.
- Oh, Day Six!

463
00:21:12,396 --> 00:21:15,732
- So I need to hand it tomorrow.
- Oh, right.

464
00:21:15,816 --> 00:21:18,235
The travel plan that I have

465
00:21:18,902 --> 00:21:20,445
is a difficult one.

466
00:21:20,946 --> 00:21:21,780
Hmm?

467
00:21:22,531 --> 00:21:23,532
What's it like?

468
00:21:23,615 --> 00:21:24,449
It's, uh…

469
00:21:25,033 --> 00:21:26,034
skiing.

470
00:21:26,618 --> 00:21:28,245
Wow! Really?

471
00:21:28,745 --> 00:21:29,955
That's so nice!

472
00:21:30,038 --> 00:21:31,123
Do you ski?

473
00:21:31,206 --> 00:21:32,541
I've never skied before.

474
00:21:32,624 --> 00:21:33,500
Oh, really?

475
00:21:33,583 --> 00:21:36,712
It's 2,000 meters above sea level.

476
00:21:36,795 --> 00:21:39,715
- It's up on this high mountain.
- Wow.

477
00:21:39,798 --> 00:21:41,091
Can you ski?

478
00:21:41,174 --> 00:21:42,509
I'm from Niigata.

479
00:21:42,592 --> 00:21:43,927
- That's right!
- Yeah.

480
00:21:44,011 --> 00:21:45,470
I grew up in the snow.

481
00:21:45,554 --> 00:21:47,973
Did you go skiing on your field trips?

482
00:21:48,056 --> 00:21:50,225
Yeah. We had ski camps too.

483
00:21:50,309 --> 00:21:51,476
I went skiing every year.

484
00:21:51,977 --> 00:21:53,020
- I see.
- Yeah.

485
00:21:53,520 --> 00:21:55,022
She's from Niigata!

486
00:21:55,564 --> 00:21:57,149
Hikakin is also from Niigata.

487
00:21:57,232 --> 00:21:59,443
He is, but you don't have to mention it.

488
00:21:59,526 --> 00:22:02,404
- Oh, yeah. About today…
- Yeah?

489
00:22:02,487 --> 00:22:05,032
Do you have any plans
after we go to the vintage shop?

490
00:22:05,115 --> 00:22:05,949
No.

491
00:22:06,033 --> 00:22:07,993
I want to go near the beach.

492
00:22:09,828 --> 00:22:11,705
Do you know Castle Hill?

493
00:22:11,788 --> 00:22:12,706
What's that?

494
00:22:13,290 --> 00:22:14,916
If you don't mind,

495
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:16,710
I want to go while the sun is out.

496
00:22:17,336 --> 00:22:20,422
I want a panoramic view
of the sea around Nice.

497
00:22:20,505 --> 00:22:21,590
I wanna see that.

498
00:22:25,177 --> 00:22:26,011
Are you cold?

499
00:22:26,511 --> 00:22:27,387
A little.

500
00:22:27,888 --> 00:22:29,014
You can wear mine.

501
00:22:29,097 --> 00:22:31,308
- It's fine. You'll be cold.
- No. Just take it.

502
00:22:31,391 --> 00:22:33,101
- You'll be cold.
- I'll be fine.

503
00:22:33,185 --> 00:22:34,353
- But…
- Here.

504
00:22:34,853 --> 00:22:37,272
- It might be small.
- Thank you.

505
00:22:38,440 --> 00:22:39,274
Here you go.

506
00:22:41,276 --> 00:22:42,402
Thank you.

507
00:22:43,403 --> 00:22:44,696
- Are you okay?
- I'm good.

508
00:22:44,780 --> 00:22:46,531
Thank you. This smells nice.

509
00:22:48,492 --> 00:22:49,493
- Okay.
- Thank you.

510
00:22:49,576 --> 00:22:51,495
- Should we eat?
- Yeah.

511
00:22:51,578 --> 00:22:53,205
- Let's eat.
- Let's eat.

512
00:22:53,288 --> 00:22:56,208
- How do I eat this? With my hands?
- I'll use my hands.

513
00:22:56,291 --> 00:22:57,459
- It's warm!
- It's warm.

514
00:23:06,426 --> 00:23:07,427
So…

515
00:23:09,846 --> 00:23:10,680
First of all,

516
00:23:11,181 --> 00:23:13,725
I really want to thank you

517
00:23:14,351 --> 00:23:16,103
for asking me out today.

518
00:23:16,603 --> 00:23:19,398
Oh, no. Thank you for coming.

519
00:23:19,481 --> 00:23:24,694
- But we had never even spoken before.
- No.

520
00:23:24,778 --> 00:23:28,365
- Did you think, "Why?"
- I wasn't sure you'd be okay with me.

521
00:23:28,448 --> 00:23:30,242
